title: Lakes Designated for Human Contact Consumption Fishery or High Quality Use, Iowa, 2004
name: Lakes Designated for Human Contact Consumption Fishery or High Quality Use, Iowa, 2004
description:
Abstract:

Lakes in Iowa that have been designated either for human  contact, human consumption, fisheries, or for high quality features in 2004 Surface Water Classification.

Purpose:

This digital, geographically referenced data set was developed by the Iowa Department of Natural Resources to carry out agency responsibilities related to management, protection, and development of Iowa's natural resources.

Supplemental_Information:

The data used to generate comes from Iowa Code Chapter 61 on  Water Quality Standards which lists all lakes that are designated and describes what those designations mean.
